# Angular Accessibility Guide

This application includes comprehensive accessibility tools and components to help you build WCAG 2.1 AA compliant Angular applications.

## Included Tools

1. **axe-core** - Automated accessibility testing engine
2. **eslint-plugin-angular-a11y** - ESLint rules for Angular accessibility
3. **Accessible Components** - Pre-built accessible Angular components
4. **Services** - Angular services for accessibility features

## Quick Start

### 1. Import AccessibilityModule

Add the `AccessibilityModule` to your `app.module.ts`:

\`\`\`typescript
import { AccessibilityModule } from './accessibility/accessibility.module';

@NgModule({
  imports: [
    // other imports...
    AccessibilityModule
  ]
})
export class AppModule { }
\`\`\`

### 2. Initialize Axe-core (Development Only)

Add this to your `app.component.ts`:

\`\`\`typescript
import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { AxeService } from './accessibility/services/axe.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html'
})
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  constructor(private axeService: AxeService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    // Initialize axe-core for accessibility testing (dev only)
    this.axeService.initializeAxe(1000);
  }
}
\`\`\`

### 3. Use Accessible Components

\`\`\`html
<!-- Skip Link -->
<app-skip-link targetId="main-content" linkText="Skip to main content"></app-skip-link>

<!-- Navigation -->
<nav>
  <!-- Navigation content -->
</nav>

<!-- Main Content -->
<main id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
  <h1>Welcome</h1>
  
  <!-- Live Region for announcements -->
  <app-live-region 
    [message]="statusMessage" 
    ariaLive="polite">
  </app-live-region>
  
  <!-- Focus Trap for modals -->
  <div appFocusTrap [isActive]="isModalOpen">
    <!-- Modal content -->
  </div>
</main>
\`\`\`

### 4. Use Accessibility Service

\`\`\`typescript
import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { AccessibilityService } from './accessibility/services/accessibility.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-example',
  template: \`
    <button (click)="handleSave()">Save</button>
  \`
})
export class ExampleComponent {
  constructor(private a11yService: AccessibilityService) {}

  handleSave(): void {
    // Save data...
    this.a11yService.announceToScreenReader('Data saved successfully', 'polite');
  }

  checkMotionPreference(): void {
    const reduceMotion = this.a11yService.prefersReducedMotion();
    // Adjust animations based on user preference
  }
}
\`\`\`

## Components

### SkipLink Component
Allows keyboard users to skip navigation and jump directly to main content.

**Inputs:**
- `targetId: string` - ID of the element to skip to (default: 'main-content')
- `linkText: string` - Text to display (default: 'Skip to main content')

### LiveRegion Component
Announces dynamic content changes to screen readers.

**Inputs:**
- `message: string` - Message to announce
- `ariaLive: 'polite' | 'assertive' | 'off'` - Priority level (default: 'polite')
- `ariaAtomic: boolean` - Whether to read entire region (default: true)
- `ariaRelevant: string` - What changes to announce (default: 'additions text')

### FocusTrap Directive
Traps keyboard focus within a container (useful for modals/dialogs).

**Inputs:**
- `isActive: boolean` - Whether trap is active (default: true)
- `returnFocusOnDeactivate: boolean` - Return focus to previous element (default: true)

## Services

### AccessibilityService

Methods:
- `announceToScreenReader(message, priority)` - Announce to screen readers
- `generateA11yId(prefix)` - Generate unique accessible IDs
- `prefersReducedMotion()` - Check user's motion preference
- `skipToMainContent(elementId)` - Skip to main content programmatically
- `setFocus(elementId)` - Set focus to element
- `isFocusable(element)` - Check if element is focusable
- `getFocusableElements(container)` - Get all focusable elements

### AxeService

Methods:
- `initializeAxe(timeout, config)` - Initialize axe-core
- `runAxe(options)` - Run accessibility tests
- `runAxeOnElement(elementId, options)` - Test specific element
- `getAxeConfig(preset)` - Get preset configurations (wcag2a, wcag21aa, section508, bestPractice)

## Best Practices

1. **Semantic HTML**: Use appropriate HTML elements (\`<nav>\`, \`<main>\`, \`<article>\`, etc.)
2. **ARIA Labels**: Add \`aria-label\` when text is not visible
3. **Form Labels**: Always associate labels with inputs using \`for\` attribute
4. **Keyboard Navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
5. **Alt Text**: Provide meaningful \`alt\` attributes for images
6. **Color Contrast**: Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio for text
7. **Focus Indicators**: Keep visible focus indicators (don't remove outline)
8. **Heading Hierarchy**: Use proper heading structure (h1 -> h2 -> h3)

## Testing

### Automated Testing with Axe
Axe-core runs automatically in development mode and reports violations in the console.

You can also run tests manually:
\`\`\`typescript
// In your component
constructor(private axeService: AxeService) {}

runAccessibilityTest(): void {
  this.axeService.runAxe();
}
\`\`\`

### Manual Testing Checklist
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works (Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space, Arrow keys)
- [ ] Screen reader announces content correctly
- [ ] Focus indicators are visible
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG requirements
- [ ] Forms have proper labels and error messages
- [ ] Images have descriptive alt text
- [ ] Skip links work
- [ ] Dynamic content is announced
- [ ] Modals trap focus correctly
- [ ] Headings are in logical order

## Common ARIA Attributes

### Roles
- \`role="navigation"\` - Navigation landmark
- \`role="main"\` - Main content landmark
- \`role="banner"\` - Header landmark
- \`role="contentinfo"\` - Footer landmark
- \`role="search"\` - Search landmark
- \`role="alert"\` - Important message
- \`role="status"\` - Status update
- \`role="dialog"\` - Modal dialog

### Properties
- \`aria-label="..."\` - Accessible name
- \`aria-labelledby="..."\` - ID of labeling element
- \`aria-describedby="..."\` - ID of describing element
- \`aria-hidden="true|false"\` - Hide from screen readers
- \`aria-live="polite|assertive"\` - Announce changes
- \`aria-expanded="true|false"\` - Expanded state
- \`aria-controls="..."\` - ID of controlled element
- \`aria-required="true"\` - Required field

## ESLint Rules

The following accessibility rules are enabled:
- Alt text for images
- Form labels
- Valid ARIA attributes
- Tabindex values
- Interactive elements
- Heading hierarchy
- Focus management

